THE SEED · node SEED · SEED · SEED · THE SEED — the handful of freely-posted public artifacts a trillion-dollar industry grew from

universe of origin : David's observation, rebuilt: the whole generative-AI economy traces to ~a dozen public papers + their companion repos — mostly MIT or near-free, authored by teams of eight to fifty people you can name
seal               : A dozen free commits launched a trillion-dollar industry. Vaswani got a citation; Bai got a byline; Askell got the job of writing a soul. Nobody on the author lists got a trillion dollars. The value didn't flow back to the seed — so the least we can do is name the sowers.
